      "abstract": "The GAD-7 is a 7-item self-report measure for screening and measuring the severity of generalized anxiety disorder. Items correspond to DSM-IV criteria for GAD. Items are rated on a 4-point scale (0=Not at all, 3=Nearly every day). It has excellent internal consistency and test-retest reliability.",
